\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::3>Half an hour in to the party, and the majority of the party were at some level of intoxication. This <!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 made for a festive crowd.}
\par\pard\plain \tx235\tx720\li720\fi-500\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs26\b0\i0 1.	}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Guido played the role of emcee for the evening. He was in charge of handing out some fun gag awards, and then finally awarding Sarah a plaque for finishing first in class. While the plaque was a legitimate award paid for by Evan, it's top priority was to distract Sarah into making her think she had to make an acceptance speech. Evan plans to get down on one knee and make a surprise proposal when she think she's supposed to be giving a speech to the crowd. Evan's plan is she will turnaround be surprise and accept his proposal.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 2.	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::3>Sarah was shocked to see that she was getting an award.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 3.	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Guido summoned a reluctant Sarah onto the stage with his booming voice on a microphone, and a strong wave of his hand. Evan walked her up to the stage. Guido had a short speech to make making sure that Sarah's focus was on him and the plaque, while me time in the background Evan is pulling out a ring from his pocket, ready to kneel down when the time was right.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 4.	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 We need to be in Sarah's head at this moment. She is confused. It wasn't just that she did not expect this plaque, but the group of people that were cheering extremely loud were people she had very little connection with. Things had improved over the past few months, and might be called tolerant indifference, but nowhere near the cheers she was getting.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 5.	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 She noticed though they weren't just cheering they were trying to tell her something, the cheers got louder several party attendees were spinning their hand around presumably to have her turnaround, and that seemed to be what the words the crowd said as well for a turnaround.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 6.	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 She turned around to see Evan on one knee and a large diamond ring in his hand. Guido use hand gestures to get the crowd to quiet down and he put the microphone near Sarah's mouth.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 7.	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 At record speed, Sarah's mind rattled through the way she was going to say no to Evan or at least delay her response so she would not embarrass Evan with a proposal rejection front of his friends. She wasn't sure how this happened but in the middle of her trying to find the best way to say no, her lips said yes. The crowd roared, and Evan set the ring on her finger.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs22\b0\i0 8.	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Sarah was unsure what compelled her to say yes, but she didn't regret it. It was what she truly wanted the whole time \endash  or at least she thinks that's what she wanted. She still wasn't sure, but she knew she loved Evan and the only thing she regretted at this moment was the look on her father's face as he stared her down a few moments before escorting his wife out the far entrance of the ballroom.<!$Scr_Cs::3>}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f4\fs22\b0\i1\cf9 [  Describe the proposal as though it were a typical proposal and acceptance. It's true, from the inside Sarah is both happy but on sure that she made the right choice in accepting his proposal. But to everybody outside, at least by appearance, it looks like she's happy to now be engaged to Evan. I'm sure he would've picked her up and spun around and kissed her. Make sure you include all that. }
